{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator_mem\"><span class=\"name\">lorentzAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">rotationGenerator_mem</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator\">rotationGenerator</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <a href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basic.html#lorentzAlgebra\">lorentzAlgebra</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The rotation generator J_i is in the Lorentz algebra. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator_mem","kind":"theorem","line":123,"name":"lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator_mem","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L123-L142"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator_mem\"><span class=\"name\">lorentzAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">boostGenerator_mem</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator\">boostGenerator</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <a href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basic.html#lorentzAlgebra\">lorentzAlgebra</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The boost generator K_i is in the Lorentz algebra. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator_mem","kind":"theorem","line":100,"name":"lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator_mem","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L100-L121"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator\"><span class=\"name\">lorentzAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">rotationGenerator</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Defs.html#Matrix\">Matrix</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sum\">⊕</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sum\">⊕</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The rotation generator J_i in the Lorentz algebra so(1,3).\n\nThis matrix generates infinitesimal rotations about the i-th axis following the right-hand rule.\nThe matrix acts only on spatial indices in the antisymmetric pattern characteristic of\nangular momentum generators.\n\n## Properties\n- Antisymmetric: J_iᵀ = -J_i\n- Traceless: tr(J_i) = 0\n- Satisfies Lorentz algebra condition: J_iᵀ η = -η J_i\n\n## Structure\n- J_0 (rotation about x-axis) : Acts on (y,z) components\n- J_1 (rotation about y-axis) : Acts on (z,x) components\n- J_2 (rotation about z-axis) : Acts on (x,y) components\n\n## Physical Meaning\nExponentiating θ·J_i produces a finite rotation by angle θ about axis i.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator","kind":"def","line":68,"name":"lorentzAlgebra.rotationGenerator","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L68-L98"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator\"><span class=\"name\">lorentzAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">boostGenerator</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Defs.html#Matrix\">Matrix</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sum\">⊕</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sum\">⊕</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span></span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The boost generator K_i in the Lorentz algebra so(1,3).\n\nThis matrix generates infinitesimal Lorentz boosts in the i-th spatial direction.\nThe matrix has non-zero entries only at positions (0, i+1) and (i+1, 0) with value 1,\nwhere we use the index convention 0 = time, 1,2,3 = space.\n\n## Properties\n- Symmetric: K_iᵀ = K_i\n- Traceless: tr(K_i) = 0\n- Satisfies Lorentz algebra condition: K_iᵀ η = -η K_i\n\n## Physical Meaning\nExponentiating β·K_i produces a finite Lorentz boost with rapidity β in direction i.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/LorentzAlgebra/Basis.html#lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator","kind":"def","line":49,"name":"lorentzAlgebra.boostGenerator","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L49-L66"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.Relativity.LorentzAlgebra.Basic","PhysLean.Meta.TODO.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.Relativity.LorentzAlgebra.Basis"}